name: optimal
trans: being the best or most desirable

name: fuel
trans: to provide power to something

name: breed
trans: to keep animals or plants for the purpose of producing young animals or plants, often for chosen qualities

name: obscure
trans: unclear and difficult to understand or see

name: imperative
trans: something that needs to be done or given attention immediately

name: aspect
trans: a particular feature of or way of thinking about something, esp. something complicated

name: diurnal
trans: happening over a period of a day, or being active or happening during the day rather than at night

name: endure
trans: to experience and bear something difficult, painful, or unpleasant

name: evolve
trans: to change or develop gradually

name: fascinate
trans: to have someone’s complete interest and attention

name: feat
trans: an act that shows skill, strength, or bravery

name: hemisphere
trans: half of the earth

name: inhabit
trans: to live in a place

name: migration
trans: movement from one region to another and often back again, esp. according to the season of the year

name: navigation
trans: the act of directing a ship, aircraft, etc. from one place to another, or the science of finding a way from one place to another

name: nocturnal
trans: of the night, or active during the night

name: observer
trans: a person who watches what happens but has no active part in it

name: species
trans: a set of animals or plants, members of which have similar characteristics to each other and which can breed with each other

name: stray
trans: to move away from a place where you should be or from a direction in which you should go

name: windswept
trans: (of places) open to and not protected from strong winds
